<p>The <code>page</code> tag includes and executes another PAD page.</p>

<h2>Basic Page Include</h2>
<pre>{open}page 'fragments/claude/subpage'{close}</pre>
<p>Result:</p>
{page 'fragments/claude/subpage'}

<h2>How It Works</h2>
<p>The <code>page</code> tag:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Executes the PHP file (pagename.php) to get data</li>
  <li>Processes the PAD template (pagename.pad)</li>
  <li>Inserts the result into the current page</li>
</ol>

<h2>Variable Scope</h2>
<p>Variables from the main page are available in included pages:</p>
<pre>Main page sets: $mainVar = 'Value from main page'
In subpage: {open}$mainVar{close}</pre>
<p>$mainVar = {$mainVar}</p>

<h2>Include from _include Directory</h2>
<p>Files in _include/ can be referenced directly:</p>
<pre>{open}snippet{close}</pre>
{snippet}

<h2>Include with Variables</h2>
<pre>{open}set userName='Alice'{close}
{open}greeting{close}</pre>
{set userName='Alice'}
{greeting}

<h2>Use Cases</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Modular page components</li>
  <li>Reusable widgets</li>
  <li>Include headers/footers</li>
  <li>Dynamic content sections</li>
</ul>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>The page tag executes both .php and .pad files. For template-only includes, use the <code>_include</code> directory or <code>get</code> tag with stored content.</p>
